                            <span>Which tool has better support for Indian languages?</span>
                            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down faq-toggle"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-answer">
                            <p>Canva Pro currently supports Hindi, Tamil, Telugu, and other regional languages better with more localized templates. Adobe Express is catching up but still has limited Indian language support.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <div class="faq-question">
                            <span>Can I pay in INR for these subscriptions?</span>
                            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down faq-toggle"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-answer">
                            <p>Yes! Both Canva and Adobe accept Indian Rupee payments directly. Canva offers annual INR billing (₹6,999/year) while Adobe charges monthly (₹399/month).</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <div class="faq-question">
                            <span>Which platform has better Diwali/Indian festival templates?</span>
                            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down faq-toggle"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-answer">
                            <p>Canva has a significantly larger collection of Indian festival templates (Diwali, Holi, Rakhi, etc.) that are culturally appropriate and ready-to-use.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <div class="faq-question">
                            <span>Is there GST charged on these subscriptions?</span>
                            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down faq-toggle"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-answer">
                            <p>Yes, both services charge applicable GST (18%) on top of the listed prices for Indian customers. The prices shown on this page include GST.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <div class="faq-question">
                            <span>Which tool works better with slow Indian internet connections?</span>
                            <i class="fas fa-chevron-down faq-toggle"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-answer">
                            <p>Canva generally performs better on slower connections due to its lighter interface. Adobe Express requires more bandwidth, especially for video editing features.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
